01:02.471 --> 01:06.306
GIRL: ♪ La, la, la, la, la, la ♪

01:06.341 --> 01:07.340
♪ La-la, la-la ♪

01:07.376 --> 01:10.377
♪ La, la, la-la, la, la, la ♪

01:10.412 --> 01:12.212
♪ La, la, la ♪

01:12.247 --> 01:14.280
♪ La, la, la, la, la... ♪

01:14.316 --> 01:15.769
Will you give it a rest?

01:16.137 --> 01:17.903
You've been at it for hours, Molly.

01:17.939 --> 01:19.038
If I want to be in the Royal Ballet,

01:19.073 --> 01:21.107
I have to practice day and night.

01:23.550 --> 01:24.916
Isn't the Royal Ballet in London?

01:24.952 --> 01:26.585
(chuckling): You're not going to London.

01:26.620 --> 01:28.174
I am, too.

01:28.209 --> 01:30.075
The Royal Ballet's
the best in the world.

01:30.637 --> 01:31.590
You can dance

01:31.625 --> 01:33.892
in Ireland, where you're with family.

01:33.927 --> 01:35.827
Where you have people to look after you.

01:35.863 --> 01:37.929
I don't need anybody to look after me.

01:37.965 --> 01:39.531
I look after meself just fine.

01:39.566 --> 01:40.932
♪ La, la, la, la ♪

01:40.968 --> 01:44.803
♪ La, la, la, la, la, la, la ♪

01:44.838 --> 01:46.772
♪ La, la, la, la ♪

01:46.807 --> 01:47.906
♪ La, la, la, la, la! ♪

01:47.941 --> 01:51.743
♪ La, la, la, la, la, la... ♪

01:51.779 --> 01:54.713
(Molly's singing echoing)

02:06.827 --> 02:11.313
("No War" by Cari Cari playing)

02:39.493 --> 02:40.926
♪ ♪

02:40.961 --> 02:43.829
♪ You fill our hearts... ♪

02:43.864 --> 02:44.896
Really?

02:44.932 --> 02:46.832
Did you say that to your mummy?

02:46.867 --> 02:47.899
That's cheeky.

02:47.935 --> 02:49.901
I will see you later, young man.

02:49.937 --> 02:51.470
Take care.

02:51.505 --> 02:52.771
And you.

02:52.806 --> 02:54.773
Have a nice day.

02:54.808 --> 02:56.875
(speaks indistinctly)

02:59.747 --> 03:00.746
(engine starts)

03:03.717 --> 03:07.753
♪ No war... ♪

03:07.788 --> 03:08.820
That pretty wife of yours...

03:08.856 --> 03:11.656
♪ No war... ♪

03:11.692 --> 03:14.626
...does she know where you spent
last Tuesday afternoon?

03:14.661 --> 03:16.561
♪ No war... ♪

03:16.597 --> 03:17.596
- (chokes)
- Huh?

03:17.631 --> 03:19.631
What... do you want?

03:19.666 --> 03:23.535
I want you to get me into the Courtenay.

03:25.639 --> 03:33.736
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

03:34.815 --> 03:36.648
(indistinct conversations)

03:36.683 --> 03:37.749
GRACE: <i>Natalie, where are you?</i>

03:37.785 --> 03:38.784
Luc's been arrested.

03:38.819 --> 03:41.720
Please, just... call me back.

03:41.755 --> 03:43.555
I need you.

03:46.627 --> 03:48.560
(Bruno breathing hard)

03:49.797 --> 03:50.796
Wow.

03:52.833 --> 03:54.733
You are a dirty cop, aren't you?

03:54.768 --> 03:56.568
(laughs)

03:56.837 --> 03:59.604
(both laugh)

04:05.579 --> 04:06.611
Don't.

04:06.647 --> 04:07.679
Stop it.

04:07.714 --> 04:08.909
What?

04:09.750 --> 04:11.616
Because it's ugly.

04:11.652 --> 04:12.651
Nah, it isn't.

04:14.588 --> 04:15.812
It's beautiful.

04:20.494 --> 04:21.526
How did you get it?

04:22.796 --> 04:25.564
Come on, tell me.

04:27.163 --> 04:28.701
Every scar has a story.

04:29.468 --> 04:30.703
Like this one.

04:31.243 --> 04:32.604
When I was a little kid,

04:32.639 --> 04:33.738
at my nan's,

04:33.774 --> 04:35.540
fell off the fire escape

04:35.576 --> 04:36.675
pretending to be a superhero.

04:40.647 --> 04:41.971
How did you get yours?

04:42.616 --> 04:44.280
That's a long story.

04:44.315 --> 04:46.751
Well... I got nowhere I need to be,

04:46.787 --> 04:48.553
I can tell you that much.

04:55.629 --> 04:57.174
I was 16.

04:58.918 --> 05:00.369
It was winter break.

05:00.404 --> 05:02.734
Um... my best friend, Ashley,

05:02.769 --> 05:04.717
was having a party, but...

05:05.539 --> 05:06.738
there was a snowstorm on the way.

05:06.773 --> 05:09.190
My parents were worried
I'd get caught in it.

05:10.577 --> 05:12.577
So, of course, once they went to bed,

05:12.613 --> 05:14.546
I snuck out and I went anyway.

05:15.997 --> 05:18.030
And it was all good, at first.

05:20.621 --> 05:22.047
Until my dad showed up.

05:23.449 --> 05:24.623
I, um...

05:26.047 --> 05:28.081
I had never seen him so angry.

05:30.810 --> 05:32.877
On the way home,
he didn't say a single word.

05:35.669 --> 05:37.014
And it was snowing.

05:37.284 --> 05:38.417
Badly.

05:38.772 --> 05:41.573
So I shut my eyes
and I just tried to sleep.

05:43.710 --> 05:46.553
And then the next thing I knew,
the whole world was spinning.

05:47.581 --> 05:49.581
♪ Take me now ♪

05:49.616 --> 05:52.450
The car skidded off
the side of the road.

05:53.388 --> 05:54.787
- ♪ See my love grown old ♪
- We...

05:55.923 --> 05:57.856
we rolled four times.

05:59.593 --> 06:01.860
I fractured my spine, and my dad, um...

06:01.895 --> 06:05.430
♪ Break me down ♪

06:05.465 --> 06:07.036
...my dad died the next day.

06:07.434 --> 06:10.435
♪ See my blood runs cold ♪

06:10.470 --> 06:11.770
I'm so sorry, Nat.

06:11.805 --> 06:12.871
If I hadn't gone to that party,

06:12.906 --> 06:14.773
Grace and I would still have a dad.

06:14.808 --> 06:16.708
♪ From the heavens ♪

06:16.743 --> 06:18.743
Everything would be different.

06:18.779 --> 06:20.745
Hey, no, no, no, don't you do that.

06:20.781 --> 06:21.813
You can't do that to yourself.

06:21.848 --> 06:22.881
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

06:23.243 --> 06:24.291
Why?

06:25.459 --> 06:27.686
- You know, it's-it's the truth.
- No, no.

06:27.721 --> 06:28.853
You had no control over that situation;

06:28.889 --> 06:31.907
you had no control
over the car, did you?

06:32.693 --> 06:34.626
You were just being a normal kid.

06:34.661 --> 06:35.727
- (phone buzzing)
- Oh, God...

06:36.690 --> 06:37.629
Sorry.

06:37.664 --> 06:38.697
- (Natalie sniffs)
- Sorry.

06:43.670 --> 06:45.467
(Natalie exhales)

06:45.502 --> 06:46.912
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah.

06:48.443 --> 06:50.509
You can answer it if you need to.

06:50.544 --> 06:52.477
No, no. There are far
more pressing matters

06:52.512 --> 06:53.578
to attend to here.

06:53.614 --> 06:55.614
♪ The breeze carried a breath ♪

06:55.682 --> 06:57.916
♪ Into the night ♪

06:57.951 --> 07:00.940
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

07:00.975 --> 07:01.808
Luc!

07:02.556 --> 07:07.425
♪ You're the shepherd's call ♪

07:09.529 --> 07:12.797
♪ Ooh, ooh... ♪

07:12.833 --> 07:13.878
Stan!

07:15.469 --> 07:17.802
- Hey. Is he okay?
- Did I not tell you to go home?

07:17.838 --> 07:19.137
- I'm not...
- You should not be seen

07:19.162 --> 07:20.472
anyplace around here.

07:20.507 --> 07:21.806
I'm not going home
until I know what's going on.

07:21.842 --> 07:22.874
Is he going to jail?

07:23.693 --> 07:24.409
I'm gonna be honest

07:24.444 --> 07:25.744
with you, Grace, all right?

07:25.779 --> 07:26.845
It is a serious charge,

07:26.880 --> 07:28.431
it is not his first offense...

07:28.466 --> 07:30.782
What about bail? I can talk to James.

07:30.817 --> 07:32.659
After you two jumped a train to Paris,

07:32.694 --> 07:34.786
bail is about as realistic
as the Tooth Fairy.

07:35.889 --> 07:37.689
You can get him off, though, right?

07:37.724 --> 07:39.691
I've gotten guys off for a lot worse

07:39.726 --> 07:41.726
than distributing a bag of coke,
so don't worry. It'll be fine.

07:41.762 --> 07:42.740
I need to see Luc.

07:44.252 --> 07:45.764
He's been through so much.

07:47.242 --> 07:48.733
Look, I'm gonna give you some advice.

07:48.769 --> 07:50.669
And I'm not gonna charge
your stepdad for it.

07:51.245 --> 07:52.737
The fact of the matter is,

07:52.773 --> 07:54.220
Luc is a drug addict.

07:54.675 --> 07:55.674
You got to move on.

07:55.709 --> 07:56.667
No.

07:57.523 --> 07:59.678
There are plenty of hot guys out there.

08:00.006 --> 08:02.166
Some even have jobs.

08:03.717 --> 08:05.583
(loud thud)

08:12.626 --> 08:13.658
- MAN: Grace!
- WOMAN: Grace!

08:13.694 --> 08:15.560
(reporters clamoring)

08:21.535 --> 08:23.435
REPORTER: Grace, did you
get high with him?

08:23.470 --> 08:25.470
- GRACE: Please...
- REPORTER: How often?

08:25.505 --> 08:26.871
Please, just...

08:28.575 --> 08:30.110
Grace, is Luc Pascal's

08:30.135 --> 08:32.577
drug use tied to Molly Ryan's murder?

08:32.611 --> 08:35.580
- (reporters clamoring)
- MAN: Stop! Get back.

08:35.615 --> 08:37.549
- Grace...
- She's been through enough.

08:37.583 --> 08:39.851
Leave her alone. Come on.

08:39.885 --> 08:41.553
- (reporters clamoring)
- Get back!

08:41.587 --> 08:43.455
- I said leave her alone.
- Grace...

08:43.490 --> 08:44.554
I said get back!

08:45.492 --> 08:46.753
- (clamoring)
- Get back!

08:47.561 --> 08:48.808
Get back!

08:49.563 --> 08:52.464
(reporters continue shouting)

08:52.499 --> 08:53.798
Get a shot. Get a shot in there.

08:53.834 --> 08:55.734
In there. In there, in there.

08:56.870 --> 08:58.470
All right.

08:58.538 --> 08:59.804
I think we lost 'em.

08:59.840 --> 09:01.740
I... I honestly don't know

09:01.775 --> 09:02.841
how I would have gotten out of there

09:02.909 --> 09:04.809
if you hadn't come to the rescue.

09:05.058 --> 09:06.746
It's not right, you know.

09:06.780 --> 09:08.780
Especially after
all you've been through.

09:08.815 --> 09:10.749
These people don't care what's right,

09:10.784 --> 09:12.281
they just want a story.

09:13.369 --> 09:14.786
I wish I could say
I was getting used to it,

09:14.821 --> 09:16.788
but they follow me, watch my every move.

09:16.823 --> 09:17.856
It's...

09:17.891 --> 09:19.724
- They're nothing but bullies.
- Come on.

09:19.760 --> 09:21.659
- I hate bullies.
- Ooh!

09:22.370 --> 09:23.795
- They broke your phone?
- Yeah.

09:23.830 --> 09:25.663
This is all such a nightmare.

09:25.699 --> 09:27.969
- Uh, can I see it?
- Sure.

09:28.735 --> 09:30.668
- (grunts)
- Sometimes, it's just

09:30.704 --> 09:32.604
- a loose SIM card.
- I really need

09:32.639 --> 09:34.572
to reach my sister, I've been
trying to call her all night,

09:34.608 --> 09:35.707
- and...
- I can fix it.

09:36.034 --> 09:37.122
You can?

09:37.744 --> 09:39.711
I just need the right tools.

09:39.780 --> 09:41.713
Actually, I've got one
at the shop I work at.

09:44.518 --> 09:45.617
Thanks so much.

09:45.652 --> 09:47.685
You've done more than enough.
I can take care of it.

09:47.721 --> 09:49.654
The shop's just walking distance,

09:49.689 --> 09:51.049
actually, but...

09:53.390 --> 09:54.692
I-If you'd rather not, I understand.

09:54.728 --> 09:56.561
You've only just met me.

09:59.385 --> 10:00.565
Hey, you know what?

10:00.600 --> 10:02.333
You've already saved me once today.

10:02.369 --> 10:03.478
If you can fix my phone...

10:03.763 --> 10:05.870
dude, you're a friend for life.

10:05.906 --> 10:07.539
Brilliant. Uh...

10:08.166 --> 10:10.508
my shop's right this way.

10:17.525 --> 10:20.277
- GUTTERIE: Hello.
- I told you, Ms. Hall is busy.

10:20.366 --> 10:22.587
That is a very pretty dress.

10:22.612 --> 10:23.830
It's very Parisian.

10:25.407 --> 10:26.172
Hello.

10:26.207 --> 10:29.042
Sorry to interrupt
your game of Candy Crush.

10:29.077 --> 10:32.646
- What is it, Gutterie?
- Your confidential informant, you know,

10:32.671 --> 10:35.104
the guy who bought the drugs
from Luc Pascal,

10:35.139 --> 10:36.983
is he well hung?

10:37.018 --> 10:38.418
- Excuse me?
- The arresting officers

10:38.453 --> 10:40.420
did perform a strip search on him

10:40.455 --> 10:43.069
before they sent him out, right?

10:43.104 --> 10:45.258
Because there's no mention of that

10:45.293 --> 10:47.360
in the paperwork there.

10:47.396 --> 10:48.502
Yeah...

10:48.537 --> 10:53.149
And the officers failed to
maintain visual contact with him

10:53.185 --> 10:55.135
until the deal was made.

10:55.170 --> 10:57.421
How are you going to convince a jury

10:57.446 --> 10:59.026
that the CI did not

10:59.061 --> 11:01.465
pull the drugs out of his own ass?

11:02.210 --> 11:04.043
Man, your coppers,

11:04.079 --> 11:05.211
they really screwed the pooch

11:05.247 --> 11:06.794
on this one, didn't they?

11:08.083 --> 11:10.216
Good help is just
so hard to find these days.

11:10.799 --> 11:12.085
You and I both know

11:12.120 --> 11:13.186
that this will not hold up in court.

11:13.221 --> 11:14.220
I want it dropped.

11:15.012 --> 11:18.158
That's for the magistrate to decide.

11:18.193 --> 11:20.093
And his docket is full
until tomorrow morning.

11:20.128 --> 11:22.030
Well, then I will bring the donuts.

11:22.291 --> 11:23.390
And we will celebrate.

11:28.170 --> 11:30.839
We've got 22 hours to get
Luc Pascal to talk.

11:31.747 --> 11:33.413
So is this your MO, hmm?

11:34.176 --> 11:36.109
Cooking breakfast for the ladies?

11:36.144 --> 11:37.977
Only the very lucky ones.

11:38.013 --> 11:39.412
Go on. Have at it.

11:39.448 --> 11:41.160
It's nicer than it looks. I promise.

11:51.470 --> 11:53.365
Don't give up my day job, yeah?

11:53.948 --> 11:55.214
I never said that.

11:57.365 --> 12:00.967
Who would've thought I'd end up
having morning-after breakfast

12:01.002 --> 12:03.765
with the detective investigating
my sister for murder?

12:04.884 --> 12:07.273
I guess your Crown Prosecutor
friend has better instincts

12:07.309 --> 12:08.272
than I thought.

12:09.698 --> 12:11.412
Yeah, well, I suppose
she sort of knows me better

12:11.446 --> 12:13.011
than I know myself.

12:15.283 --> 12:16.532
Wait a minute.

12:16.846 --> 12:18.042
Were you two a...

12:18.078 --> 12:18.640
What?

12:18.665 --> 12:22.222
You and Gwendolyn Hall.
Were you two a thing?

12:22.257 --> 12:23.289
No.

12:23.325 --> 12:25.358
Not, well, not like a thing...

12:25.393 --> 12:26.776
I knew it.

12:27.229 --> 12:29.128
Well, it's over anyway.

12:29.164 --> 12:30.918
- Ancient history.
- (phone chimes)

12:34.959 --> 12:36.471
Oh, my God.

12:37.239 --> 12:39.615
I have 11 messages from Grace.

12:40.275 --> 12:41.456
Everything all right?

12:44.145 --> 12:47.046
Luc's been arrested. For drugs.

12:48.149 --> 12:50.116
Grace spent all night at Scotland Yard.

12:51.871 --> 12:53.656
Her cell phone's off.

12:54.486 --> 12:55.703
I'm sure she's fine.

12:55.738 --> 12:56.710
No, she's not fine.

12:56.745 --> 12:59.459
She was up all night,
she's probably just sleeping now.

12:59.929 --> 13:02.095
Yeah, there's no answer
at our hotel room.

13:02.130 --> 13:04.030
- I'd better go.
- Do me a favor,

13:04.065 --> 13:06.065
will you just sit down,
finish your breakfast.

13:06.101 --> 13:07.367
I'll make you a coffee.

13:16.011 --> 13:17.310
You know what? You're right.

13:17.625 --> 13:19.412
You should...
you should go and check on her.

13:19.447 --> 13:21.257
Thanks for understanding.

13:33.060 --> 13:34.427
What the hell do you think you're doing?

13:34.856 --> 13:37.263
Even after your chat
with Internal Affairs,

13:37.299 --> 13:39.745
you're still not answering
my texts, taking my calls.

13:39.781 --> 13:40.847
I was getting worried.

13:41.336 --> 13:43.369
But I can see now
you've been quite busy.

13:43.405 --> 13:45.171
Sexy beast, that one.

13:45.206 --> 13:46.339
Look, I did what you asked.

13:46.374 --> 13:48.308
I'm not even on the Molly Ryan
investigation anymore.

13:48.343 --> 13:51.244
- I'm no use to you now.
- Don't sell yourself short, Detective.

13:51.279 --> 13:53.008
You're of tremendous use.

13:53.348 --> 13:56.162
You still have the vial of
Molly Ryan's blood, don't you?

13:58.627 --> 14:00.675
Find a viable suspect
for the girl's murder,

14:01.122 --> 14:02.892
dab a little blood on their clothing,

14:02.927 --> 14:06.334
and close this case once and for all.

14:06.955 --> 14:08.988
I am not planting evidence.

14:09.923 --> 14:10.889
Since when?

14:17.072 --> 14:20.006
♪ ♪

14:26.181 --> 14:28.494
Didn't think it'd be so busy
this time of day.

14:28.950 --> 14:29.916
I need a drink.

14:30.118 --> 14:31.384
Don't get any ideas.

14:33.154 --> 14:35.021
I'm sure your voters would love to know

14:35.056 --> 14:37.085
how their member of Parliament
spends his salary.

14:39.375 --> 14:42.061
You ran your last campaign
on family values, didn't you?

14:43.818 --> 14:45.431
I'm doing everything you ask of me.

14:45.805 --> 14:47.333
Keep it that way.

14:48.249 --> 14:50.182
Grace, it's Roz.

14:50.372 --> 14:51.695
Any news on Luc?

14:52.440 --> 14:53.544
Call me back.

14:55.937 --> 14:57.443
Is everything to your liking,
Mr. Purferoy?

14:58.529 --> 15:00.279
Yes, quite.

15:02.208 --> 15:04.217
This is my cousin, Kevin McGee.

15:04.252 --> 15:05.251
In from Ireland for his birthday.

15:05.286 --> 15:07.253
Thought I'd show him the sights.

15:07.288 --> 15:08.354
Nice to meet you, mate.

15:08.825 --> 15:10.356
I didn't know you had family in Ireland.

15:10.891 --> 15:13.192
Oh, yes, there are Purferoys
as far afield

15:13.228 --> 15:14.765
as Nova Scotia, Canada.

15:18.397 --> 15:20.132
Well, cousin or not,

15:20.812 --> 15:22.940
you know we have
a strict vetting process here.

15:23.338 --> 15:24.555
For all guests.

15:25.692 --> 15:26.721
Yes, of course.

15:26.757 --> 15:28.648
Especially when
they're IRA sympathizers.

15:30.104 --> 15:32.145
Oh, you're talking about this, are you?

15:32.617 --> 15:34.640
Oh, I got that when I was a wee lad.

15:35.081 --> 15:37.517
My brother's mate, Seamus,
wee bit older.

15:37.553 --> 15:39.747
He had one,
we wanted to be tough like him.

15:39.772 --> 15:41.254
I didn't even know what it meant.

15:41.289 --> 15:42.989
(both chuckle)

15:43.258 --> 15:45.024
(soft chuckle)

15:47.092 --> 15:49.195
You understand our policy
toward unvetted guests

15:49.230 --> 15:51.452
is to kindly ask them to leave
the premises immediately.

15:54.299 --> 15:56.576
But considering
your reputation in the community

15:56.612 --> 15:58.813
and your loyal patronage,

15:59.174 --> 16:00.557
I'm going to make an exception.

16:00.592 --> 16:02.008
Just this once.

16:02.043 --> 16:03.009
COLIN: Thank you, Finch.

16:03.044 --> 16:04.151
I'll remember that.

16:04.187 --> 16:05.240
You're a gentleman.

16:05.807 --> 16:06.739
Shall we?

16:20.428 --> 16:21.994
See who you fancy.

16:22.030 --> 16:23.930
♪ She has got me running ♪

16:25.400 --> 16:29.302
♪ Faster than the wind blows ♪

16:31.019 --> 16:32.151
Ariel will take care of things for you.

16:32.176 --> 16:33.601
♪ Sorrow without silence ♪

16:36.411 --> 16:39.178
♪ Built the walls that hid you. ♪

16:45.320 --> 16:46.476
Wow.

16:47.255 --> 16:49.122
When you said you worked at a shop,

16:49.157 --> 16:51.190
I never would've had you pegged
as a tailor.

16:51.226 --> 16:52.258
I'm not.

16:52.293 --> 16:53.259
Not yet.

16:53.730 --> 16:55.194
I'm an apprentice.

16:55.230 --> 16:58.325
Mr. Hoyt, he's the tailor,
he owns the shop.

16:58.414 --> 16:59.479
Is he here?

17:00.235 --> 17:01.346
No.

17:02.270 --> 17:04.693
Shop's closed, but I've got the key.

17:04.982 --> 17:07.173
Mr. Hoyt trusts me
just like he did my father.

17:08.328 --> 17:09.175
He was a tailor

17:09.210 --> 17:11.098
in this very shop before he died.

17:12.012 --> 17:13.739
He sat right there.

17:17.478 --> 17:19.152
I lost my dad when I was nine.

17:19.738 --> 17:21.087
I know how hard it can be.

17:23.838 --> 17:25.042
It wasn't too hard.

17:26.060 --> 17:27.627
He wasn't very nice to me.

17:28.738 --> 17:30.062
All right.

17:30.405 --> 17:31.898
Let's give it a go.

17:44.769 --> 17:46.312
Molly had a dress

17:46.347 --> 17:47.642
exactly like this.

17:48.954 --> 17:50.249
She did?

17:51.834 --> 17:53.953
That's an odd coincidence.

17:55.970 --> 17:57.036
Yeah.

17:57.764 --> 17:58.830
It is.

17:58.876 --> 18:01.327
I'm doing alterations for a customer.

18:01.516 --> 18:02.963
Mrs. Brambley.

18:04.399 --> 18:06.675
She's lost a bit of weight,
I'm taking it in for her.

18:14.312 --> 18:16.178
Look, her bed wasn't slept in.

18:16.214 --> 18:17.280
She never came back here last night.

18:17.315 --> 18:18.414
Have you heard from Gutterie?

18:18.449 --> 18:21.250
I mean, he saw her this morning
at the police station.

18:21.286 --> 18:22.285
It's just, it's not like her

18:22.320 --> 18:24.253
to disappear like this.

18:25.790 --> 18:28.061
Natalie, is it possible
that Grace has just...

18:28.806 --> 18:29.838
gone on the run again?

18:30.228 --> 18:31.922
No, no, of course not.

18:31.957 --> 18:34.196
Luc gets arrested, Grace panics,
she jumps on a train...

18:34.232 --> 18:37.266
No, absolutely not, I mean, not
after what happened last time.

18:37.302 --> 18:38.716
She knows better than that.

18:39.723 --> 18:41.139
Right.

18:41.272 --> 18:43.105
I know my sister.

18:43.141 --> 18:44.888
Her phone does not leave her hand.

18:44.924 --> 18:46.475
It's been over an hour
since her last voice mail.

18:46.511 --> 18:48.110
- I...
- (phone chimes)

18:50.114 --> 18:52.014
Oh, damn it.

18:52.387 --> 18:54.417
- What is it?
- It's just a news alert.

18:54.452 --> 18:56.452
I get them whenever Grace's name
shows up in the press.

18:57.013 --> 18:58.421
Wait, what?

19:00.158 --> 19:02.124
"Grace Atwood with New Boy Toy

19:02.160 --> 19:04.026
after French Lover Lands in Lockup"?

19:04.062 --> 19:05.962
BRUNO: What the hell?

19:05.997 --> 19:07.964
There you see Grace's new man
playing "My Bodyguard"

19:07.999 --> 19:09.065
with the possible killer.

19:09.100 --> 19:11.067
Fun never stops
for Grace Atwood now, does it?

19:11.102 --> 19:13.402
Reporting from outside
New Scotland Yard,

19:13.438 --> 19:15.438
this is Veena Patel, and that's...

19:15.473 --> 19:17.006
The Story.

19:18.476 --> 19:20.743
- Do you know this guy?
- No.

19:20.966 --> 19:22.962
No, I've never seen him
before in my life, I...

19:26.317 --> 19:27.812
What if he's done something to Grace?

19:28.386 --> 19:29.452
- Natalie, don't get ahead of yourself.
- But you've read

19:29.487 --> 19:31.387
what people have said about her,
they're out for blood.

19:31.422 --> 19:33.356
It's social media, they hate everybody.

19:33.391 --> 19:35.224
Not everyone gets death threats.

19:36.461 --> 19:40.196
♪ ♪

19:40.231 --> 19:43.036
Here we are. Your lovely
lady should be on her way.

19:43.071 --> 19:45.157
Brilliant. Where's the, uh, loo?

19:46.270 --> 19:48.270
Just down the hall to the left.

20:03.187 --> 20:05.121
(woman laughing)

20:18.269 --> 20:20.136
- Good to see you again.
- Good to see you as well.

20:20.171 --> 20:22.038
(indistinct chatter)

20:47.465 --> 20:49.498
(indistinct chatter)

21:04.449 --> 21:05.381
(bang)

21:16.360 --> 21:17.326
(keys jingling)

21:22.400 --> 21:24.333
(hinges creaking)

21:35.213 --> 21:37.179
♪ ♪

21:39.250 --> 21:40.840
Hey, you.

21:41.285 --> 21:43.285
What are you doing back here?
It's for employees only.

21:43.321 --> 21:45.087
I must've took a wrong turn.

21:45.425 --> 21:46.156
I'm new here.

21:46.190 --> 21:47.189
The lounge is this way, isn't it?

21:47.225 --> 21:48.642
You just stand where you are.

21:48.667 --> 21:50.692
Do not move.

21:51.815 --> 21:53.716
Control, this is Halloran. Come in.

21:55.973 --> 21:57.539
KALEY: There you are!

22:00.438 --> 22:02.725
Uh, I thought I lost you.

22:03.074 --> 22:04.473
(chuckles)

22:04.509 --> 22:07.076
It's, um, this way, darling.

22:07.111 --> 22:09.445
Uh, don't, um, worry about him.

22:09.480 --> 22:11.013
It's his first visit.

22:12.450 --> 22:14.483
(door closes)

22:15.161 --> 22:16.452
What are you doing?

22:16.487 --> 22:17.917
There are cameras everywhere.

22:19.056 --> 22:20.916
What are you doing here?

22:24.397 --> 22:25.739
Did you sneak in?

22:31.248 --> 22:33.361
I told you I need answers.

22:34.785 --> 22:36.238
And I'm gonna get 'em.

22:37.705 --> 22:40.209
Do you have any idea what they do

22:40.244 --> 22:42.244
to people who get
caught sneaking in here?

22:43.414 --> 22:45.247
I'm not gonna get caught, though, am I?

22:48.286 --> 22:51.187
Thanks to me.

22:52.256 --> 22:53.681
Now...

22:54.325 --> 22:56.258
shh, be quiet, okay?

22:56.294 --> 22:58.765
And play along.

22:59.330 --> 23:02.778
They can see everything
that goes on in this room.

23:16.180 --> 23:17.779
That's all of it.

23:21.379 --> 23:23.118
Anything I can help you with?

23:23.154 --> 23:26.055
I just wanted to double back, reexamine

23:26.090 --> 23:27.412
everything we have so far.

23:28.708 --> 23:30.025
And to see if there's anything

23:30.061 --> 23:31.460
DS Bruno missed.

23:31.906 --> 23:33.062
I didn't say that.

23:33.097 --> 23:34.096
Gwen, look,

23:34.131 --> 23:35.721
whatever happened between you two,

23:35.756 --> 23:37.399
Bruno's a damn good copper.

23:40.104 --> 23:41.503
(sighs)

23:45.318 --> 23:46.289
BRUNO: <i>I promise you we're</i>

23:46.325 --> 23:47.855
gonna find him... I've got an idea.

23:47.891 --> 23:49.378
All right.

23:49.413 --> 23:53.315
And here... is our man.

23:53.351 --> 23:54.383
If he's in our system, we should

23:54.418 --> 23:56.106
get a hit off facial recognition.

23:58.940 --> 24:01.323
Grace has always been
too trusting of people.

24:01.832 --> 24:02.864
Come on, come on.

24:03.361 --> 24:04.326
(beeps)

24:04.362 --> 24:05.803
(groans)

24:07.711 --> 24:10.165
Whoever he is, he's never
been arrested for anything.

24:10.201 --> 24:12.368
I-I wish that made me feel better.

24:12.403 --> 24:14.203
But if he was harmless,

24:14.238 --> 24:16.171
I would've heard from her by now.

24:18.711 --> 24:20.142
I know that face.

24:26.817 --> 24:28.217
GRACE: You almost finished?

24:28.252 --> 24:29.218
Yeah.

24:29.253 --> 24:30.432
Getting there.

24:32.223 --> 24:33.672
Does it bother you?

24:34.292 --> 24:36.158
All the things the bullies say?

24:36.992 --> 24:38.160
Not anymore.

24:38.229 --> 24:41.030
Um... look, I should

24:41.065 --> 24:42.480
- probably get going...
- It bothers me.

24:42.515 --> 24:45.034
I wasn't very sporty out in the pitch.

24:45.069 --> 24:46.502
So the kids, they'd have a go at me.

24:46.537 --> 24:48.170
But I fought back.

24:48.784 --> 24:50.472
I even broke a boy's arm once.

24:50.870 --> 24:54.043
(chuckles) Tripped him
when he wasn't looking.

24:54.711 --> 24:56.478
But he knew it was me.

24:56.514 --> 24:58.559
He never mocked me again.

25:03.454 --> 25:04.420
All right.

25:04.455 --> 25:07.022
I think I have it.

25:13.719 --> 25:15.364
Wait! Grace!

25:15.399 --> 25:16.999
I can explain, uh...

25:17.034 --> 25:19.335
Please just listen to me... please!

25:19.370 --> 25:20.369
Unlock the door!

25:20.404 --> 25:22.004
Just wait! Just wait!

25:22.039 --> 25:23.910
I want to leave now. Open the door.

25:23.945 --> 25:26.375
Listen to me... you need to
hear my side of all of this.

25:26.410 --> 25:28.377
Listen... Stop! Stop!

25:28.412 --> 25:30.346
(grunting): Grace, stop.

25:30.381 --> 25:31.447
- Grace, please.
- Let go!

25:31.482 --> 25:33.248
Stop that. (grunts)

25:33.284 --> 25:34.450
Stay. Just please, listen to me.

25:34.485 --> 25:37.286
No, don't leave.

25:43.041 --> 25:46.228
Look what you've done now.

25:49.610 --> 25:51.610
Marguerite will be with you today.

25:51.842 --> 25:54.502
- ***
- Very well.

25:55.985 --> 25:58.005
Do you have any idea where Kaley is?

25:59.855 --> 26:02.139
She should be with Gentleman 33.

26:03.859 --> 26:04.958
How long's it been?

26:04.994 --> 26:06.283
Almost ten minutes.

26:06.549 --> 26:07.581
Does Finch know?

26:10.800 --> 26:11.899
Okay.

26:11.934 --> 26:14.868
Tell the gentleman I'll
be with him right away.

26:25.848 --> 26:27.781
Kaley, what are you doing?

26:30.279 --> 26:33.153
Ambassador Gregson,
the focus of my foundation

26:33.189 --> 26:35.106
is to bring relief supplies
to the north,

26:35.141 --> 26:38.156
which as you're well aware,
is controlled by warlords.

26:38.828 --> 26:41.128
- Yes, yes.
- (knocking)

26:41.163 --> 26:42.843
Frightful stuff.

26:43.766 --> 26:46.133
Ah, eh, a military escort

26:46.168 --> 26:47.701
is exactly what we had in mind.

26:47.736 --> 26:48.989
Thank you.

26:51.059 --> 26:52.739
Where's my Irish ginger?

26:52.775 --> 26:54.775
I'm terribly sorry, Your Highness.

26:54.810 --> 26:56.076
Don't you dare call me that.

26:57.146 --> 26:58.123
Not in here.

26:59.048 --> 27:00.235
Right.

27:01.050 --> 27:02.749
Apologies. Our girl is out ill today,

27:02.785 --> 27:05.119
but I'm having another one
sent in straight away.

27:05.154 --> 27:06.163
Out sick?

27:07.022 --> 27:08.689
I just saw her last night.

27:08.724 --> 27:10.657
Apparently, it hit her quite suddenly.

27:10.693 --> 27:13.060
But I'm sure you'll be pleased
with another one of our girls.

27:13.095 --> 27:14.962
I don't take kindly to people
who muck me about.

27:14.997 --> 27:16.663
Did Molly muck you about?

27:23.072 --> 27:26.106
What exactly are you insinuating?

27:26.860 --> 27:28.143
Nothing.

27:28.940 --> 27:31.045
Nothing at all. I'm sorry.

27:31.080 --> 27:32.980
I...

27:33.015 --> 27:35.380
I suppose I'm still upset.

27:37.393 --> 27:38.559
About Molly.

27:51.000 --> 27:52.966
Sometimes I think
she was the only person

27:53.275 --> 27:54.935
who truly understood me.

27:58.007 --> 27:58.972
(quiet laugh)

28:02.188 --> 28:03.597
(door opens)

28:04.880 --> 28:06.893
Mrs. Harris, when you showed me
this picture

28:06.929 --> 28:08.861
of your little boy...

28:09.818 --> 28:11.885
why didn't you tell me that
he was a fully grown man?

28:11.921 --> 28:13.887
Neville will always be my little boy.

28:13.923 --> 28:15.252
Now, what's this all about?

28:15.277 --> 28:16.686
Um, my sister's missing.

28:16.711 --> 28:18.926
And Neville was the last
person she was seen with.

28:18.961 --> 28:20.973
BRUNO: Her sister was Molly
Ryan's flatmate.

28:20.998 --> 28:22.327
The same girl who was photographed

28:22.352 --> 28:23.343
from this very apartment.

28:23.378 --> 28:25.422
The same girl who was
murdered across the street.

28:27.803 --> 28:29.277
You're not suggesting...

28:31.874 --> 28:33.290
Neville is a gentle boy.

28:33.326 --> 28:34.619
He would never hurt anybody.

28:34.654 --> 28:35.651
Did he ever take an interest in

28:35.687 --> 28:37.432
any of the women from the neighborhood?

28:37.467 --> 28:39.394
You mean, like, bothering them? No.

28:39.715 --> 28:41.393
No. My son keeps to himself.

28:41.428 --> 28:43.342
He spends his time
on his sewing machine.

28:43.367 --> 28:44.751
Not hassling women.

28:44.787 --> 28:46.552
"Sewing machine," but he...

28:46.889 --> 28:48.417
There's no sewing machine here.

28:49.951 --> 28:51.086
Well, no...

28:51.121 --> 28:52.260
Does he have a workplace?

28:53.195 --> 28:54.127
Take classes somewhere?

28:54.163 --> 28:55.277
Have a studio?

28:55.831 --> 28:58.065
Look, I told you
my son didn't do anything wrong.

28:58.380 --> 28:59.218
He couldn't.

28:59.254 --> 29:00.423
BRUNO: Mrs. Harris,
I understand that you're

29:00.458 --> 29:02.313
just trying to protect your boy, I do.

29:02.338 --> 29:04.443
And you know what... I even believe you

29:04.468 --> 29:07.507
when you tell me that you don't
think he's done anything wrong.

29:07.532 --> 29:10.182
But the thing is sometimes
the people that we love,

29:10.557 --> 29:11.566
well, we don't know them

29:11.601 --> 29:12.539
as well as we think we do.

29:12.574 --> 29:14.114
Sometimes they surprise us.

29:14.149 --> 29:17.084
Sometimes, you know,
they just make a mistake.

29:17.119 --> 29:20.053
Now, we... we want to protect Neville.

29:20.089 --> 29:23.657
We want to help him make sure
that he doesn't make a mistake

29:23.692 --> 29:25.095
that will change the rest of his life.

29:25.462 --> 29:28.150
Now the only way that we can
help him is if you help us.

29:32.067 --> 29:33.133
Hey, there.

29:33.168 --> 29:35.068
You all right?

29:35.104 --> 29:36.696
It's okay.

29:38.073 --> 29:39.331
You bumped your head when you slipped...

29:39.367 --> 29:40.107
You pushed me.

29:45.695 --> 29:46.913
Molly had a stalker,

29:46.949 --> 29:48.115
and it was you... wasn't it?

29:51.086 --> 29:52.085
You stole that dress.

29:52.121 --> 29:54.563
You stole her... stuffed animal.

29:54.599 --> 29:58.418
No, I wanted something
to remember her by.

30:01.930 --> 30:04.241
I didn't kill her if that's
what you're thinking.

30:04.867 --> 30:07.034
I swear, I never even touched Molly.

30:07.699 --> 30:10.037
But I'm not gonna lie.

30:10.072 --> 30:11.938
I wanted to. I quite fancied her...

30:11.974 --> 30:13.006
You didn't even know her.

30:13.042 --> 30:14.041
Yes!

30:14.076 --> 30:15.635
I did.

30:16.332 --> 30:17.878
In a way.

30:17.913 --> 30:19.913
I watched her from my window.

30:19.948 --> 30:21.948
I would've never harmed her!

30:21.984 --> 30:26.239
I wish I could've protected her
like I protected you today...

30:26.264 --> 30:27.025
I get it.

30:28.708 --> 30:29.990
Look...

30:30.605 --> 30:32.446
I get it, Neville.

30:35.295 --> 30:36.361
You're a good guy. You really are.

30:36.396 --> 30:38.540
Molly would've liked you.

30:38.889 --> 30:40.265
You think?

30:40.992 --> 30:43.643
Molly had a thing for sweet guys

30:43.678 --> 30:45.670
with a heart of gold.

30:49.810 --> 30:51.209
I knew it.

30:51.244 --> 30:52.277
I-I should've spoken to her.

30:52.312 --> 30:55.280
I-I just get so bloody nervous.

30:55.315 --> 30:56.681
(screams)

31:05.625 --> 31:08.193
(grunting)

31:08.228 --> 31:10.161
Wait! Wait! Stop!

31:10.197 --> 31:12.163
(Neville grunting)

31:18.205 --> 31:19.204
(tires screeching)

31:21.241 --> 31:23.208
Stop it, Grace.

31:26.185 --> 31:27.757
You crazy, girl.

31:28.120 --> 31:29.496
You shouldn't have hurt me.

31:29.521 --> 31:32.155
- Let me go!
- Y-You'll tell on me.

31:32.191 --> 31:34.581
You're not nice, like Molly,
you're a monster,

31:34.616 --> 31:36.932
just like everybody says here.

31:37.796 --> 31:39.229
(tires screeching, siren wailing)

31:39.264 --> 31:42.065
GRACE: Help me!

31:42.100 --> 31:44.968
Grace! Drop that blade,
Neville, drop it right now.

31:46.104 --> 31:47.237
Natalie!

31:47.272 --> 31:49.039
You-you don't understand.

31:49.074 --> 31:50.974
She attacked me, I swear, you have...

31:51.009 --> 31:52.108
Just listen to me for a second.

31:52.144 --> 31:54.269
Sh-She did this to me.

31:55.934 --> 31:56.980
GRACE: Natalie!

31:57.015 --> 31:57.981
I had to escape.

31:58.016 --> 31:59.082
Be quiet!

31:59.117 --> 32:00.116
Uh, please,

32:00.152 --> 32:02.118
back up, both of you.

32:02.154 --> 32:04.571
We're not gonna hurt you.
We just need you to let her go.

32:04.606 --> 32:05.515
No.

32:06.600 --> 32:07.553
Natalie...

32:10.062 --> 32:11.356
That's my sister, Neville.

32:11.849 --> 32:13.421
I love her very much, okay?

32:13.457 --> 32:15.240
I wouldn't want anything
to happen to her.

32:16.101 --> 32:17.968
Neville, we spoke with your mother.

32:18.003 --> 32:19.400
My mum?

32:19.972 --> 32:21.037
Why?

32:21.073 --> 32:23.873
Because we know how much
she cares about you.

32:23.909 --> 32:25.875
As much as I care about my sister.

32:27.726 --> 32:29.692
How would your mom feel if you hurt her?

32:34.052 --> 32:36.920
You know how upset
that would make her, don't you?

32:38.023 --> 32:40.345
She would be so disappointed in you.

32:43.028 --> 32:44.504
Please, Neville.

32:50.936 --> 32:52.836
(grunts)

32:52.871 --> 32:53.903
BRUNO: That's enough!

32:53.939 --> 32:55.905
You're under arrest, all right?

32:58.877 --> 32:59.909
It's okay, Grace.

32:59.945 --> 33:02.178
It's okay.

33:07.819 --> 33:08.818
(clears throat)

33:16.862 --> 33:18.828
- (clears throat)
- Roz.

33:18.864 --> 33:20.830
(clears throat) You scared me.

33:20.866 --> 33:24.200
- Hi.
- Why the bloody hell

33:24.236 --> 33:27.137
did you sneak Patrick Ryan
into the club?

33:27.172 --> 33:28.238
I didn't. Okay?

33:28.273 --> 33:29.627
He was just standing there,

33:29.652 --> 33:31.174
and he was in the corridor,
about  get caught,

33:31.209 --> 33:33.743
- and I...
- So you shagged him.

33:36.148 --> 33:37.213
It was just pretend.

33:39.251 --> 33:40.701
(sighs)

33:40.737 --> 33:41.847
Why?

33:43.155 --> 33:45.221
- Are you jealous?
- This isn't a bloody joke!

33:45.257 --> 33:47.023
Molly's brother broke into
Finch's office.

33:47.059 --> 33:49.503
He stole the client ledger.

33:52.230 --> 33:53.436
God...

33:53.472 --> 33:55.198
Finch is on a warpath, Kaley.

33:55.233 --> 33:58.168
If he finds out you had
anything to do with it,

33:58.203 --> 33:59.871
he's going to hunt us down

33:59.896 --> 34:01.466
and kill us both.

34:05.110 --> 34:06.142
(hinges creaking)

34:29.228 --> 34:32.081
_

34:46.818 --> 34:48.784
♪ ♪

34:54.926 --> 34:55.958
(sighs)

34:55.994 --> 34:57.927
Come on, Pepper, get on with it.

35:03.001 --> 35:04.734
Finch. What...

35:04.770 --> 35:05.727
What brings you out here?

35:05.762 --> 35:07.640
You and your cousin...

35:07.675 --> 35:09.180
you're pretty close, are you?

35:10.947 --> 35:13.037
Relatively.

35:14.072 --> 35:15.912
Are you being straight with me,
Mr. Purferoy?

35:18.818 --> 35:19.915
Look, Finch...

35:19.951 --> 35:21.275
I'd appreciate some honesty.

35:21.311 --> 35:22.886
The bloke was threatening
to tell my wife

35:22.921 --> 35:24.589
if I didn't get him in.
What was I supposed to do?

35:24.624 --> 35:26.347
I thought he just nted
to knob a fancy girl.

35:26.383 --> 35:28.212
He wasn't there to knob
a fancy girl, you prat.

35:28.237 --> 35:29.826
He was there to nick something of mine.

35:30.929 --> 35:32.265
Something very vuable.

35:33.498 --> 35:34.931
Oh, God.

35:34.966 --> 35:36.520
FINCH: What's the man's real name?

35:36.902 --> 35:38.161
I don't know.

35:38.449 --> 35:39.882
He didn't tell me.

35:40.238 --> 35:41.204
Are you lying to me?

35:42.874 --> 35:44.256
Because you lied to me before.

35:45.176 --> 35:46.743
You looked me right in the eye,

35:46.778 --> 35:48.164
just like you're doing n

35:53.852 --> 35:55.185
Finch, what are you...?

35:55.220 --> 35:56.186
(grunts)

35:57.222 --> 35:59.088
(whining)

36:01.089 --> 36:03.022
♪ ♪

36:30.452 --> 36:32.385
♪ ♪

37:00.879 --> 37:03.580
- (door opens)
- PIKE: Couldn't you find the lights?

37:04.392 --> 37:05.950
I suppose congratulations are in order.

37:06.579 --> 37:08.103
- (clears throat)
- What for?

37:08.711 --> 37:11.741
For closing the Molly Ryan case,
you humble bastard.

37:11.776 --> 37:13.857
- (laughs softly)
- You was right all along.

37:13.892 --> 37:15.859
It was the stalker
that killed her, after all.

37:18.162 --> 37:18.895
Neville Harris

37:18.930 --> 37:20.864
was the stalker all right,
but he didn't kill her.

37:20.899 --> 37:21.998
What?

37:22.408 --> 37:23.867
Molly's killer was right-handed.

37:23.902 --> 37:25.001
The autopsy was very clear about that.

37:25.036 --> 37:26.474
But Neville...

37:27.529 --> 37:28.905
left-handed.

37:29.376 --> 37:30.874
These are all his scissors.

37:31.217 --> 37:32.876
They're all left-handed.

37:35.660 --> 37:36.946
Well, I'll be damned.

37:38.016 --> 37:39.816
(sniffles)

37:39.851 --> 37:40.984
Here's something that'll cheer you up.

37:41.489 --> 37:43.740
Stan's positive he'll get Luc off.

37:45.422 --> 37:46.555
Oh, thank God.

37:46.999 --> 37:48.082
When will he be out?

37:48.118 --> 37:49.524
NATALIE:
Hopefully, first thing tomorrow,

37:49.560 --> 37:51.589
after they go before the magistrate.

37:52.156 --> 37:54.090
I wish I could see him tonight.

37:57.501 --> 37:59.067
Grace, I want you to know...

37:59.370 --> 38:00.960
I'm so sorry.

38:00.995 --> 38:04.168
Why? None of this is your fault.

38:04.203 --> 38:05.849
I should've stayed with you
at the gallery.

38:06.310 --> 38:08.410
I would've been there
when Luc was arrested;

38:08.445 --> 38:09.722
I would've been there
with you at the station

38:09.747 --> 38:11.111
and then when that creep showed up,

38:11.136 --> 38:12.191
I wouldn't have let him come near you.

38:12.216 --> 38:15.835
Nat... you are my freakin' rock.

38:17.068 --> 38:18.597
You dropped everything for me

38:18.622 --> 38:21.127
and I am beyond grateful.

38:21.525 --> 38:24.137
The least you deserve is
a hook-up with that cute cop.

38:24.195 --> 38:24.844
(Natalie chuckles)

38:26.563 --> 38:27.462
How was it?

38:28.453 --> 38:29.949
Did he cuff you?

38:30.467 --> 38:31.688
(Natalie scoffs, Grace giggles)

38:31.724 --> 38:32.555
Stop it.

38:33.404 --> 38:35.370
He's definitely hot.

38:40.344 --> 38:41.948
Grace, what are you doing?

38:42.017 --> 38:43.378
I can't sit around here.

38:43.892 --> 38:45.061
I need to get out.

38:45.282 --> 38:47.249
What? Now?

38:48.132 --> 38:49.587
Let's go dancing.

38:50.724 --> 38:52.161
- You're serious?
- Why not?

38:52.196 --> 38:53.558
After the day you've had?

38:53.583 --> 38:55.047
Your boyfriend's arrested,

38:55.082 --> 38:56.391
you've been through hell.

38:56.427 --> 38:57.818
I mean, get some sleep.

38:57.843 --> 38:59.032
I'm not tired.

38:59.067 --> 39:01.949
I just... I can't be cooped up anymore.

39:01.984 --> 39:03.365
I need to get out,

39:03.400 --> 39:06.018
put everything out of my head
for a few hours.

39:07.563 --> 39:08.667
Come on.

39:10.254 --> 39:11.267
Please?

39:12.409 --> 39:15.210
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

39:15.245 --> 39:17.345
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

39:17.381 --> 39:18.540
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

39:18.565 --> 39:21.283
When was the last time you went dancing?

39:21.351 --> 39:23.937
♪ I got ten fingers to the sky ♪

39:23.972 --> 39:25.420
♪ My back to the wall,
my white bag high ♪

39:25.456 --> 39:28.323
- No
- ♪ Hair, lips, just like a gun ♪

39:28.358 --> 39:29.370
- ♪ She's got silver bullets ♪

39:29.395 --> 39:30.053
- Yeah.
- No.

39:30.088 --> 39:31.393
- ♪ On her tongue ♪
- Yes.

39:31.428 --> 39:33.261
- ♪ He's deep under her spell ♪
- Please.

39:33.297 --> 39:34.429
♪ I'm screamin' out
but it just won't help ♪

39:34.465 --> 39:37.399
♪ I think I'm cursed ♪

39:37.434 --> 39:40.202
- ♪ I had him first ♪
- You know you want to.

39:40.237 --> 39:41.320
♪ Adeline, have mercy ♪

39:41.345 --> 39:44.339
- Yeah, why not?
- ♪ You don't want to break my heart ♪

39:44.374 --> 39:46.208
♪ Take what's mine, don't hurt me ♪

39:46.243 --> 39:47.442
♪ Steal my money, steal my car ♪

39:47.478 --> 39:50.412
I just want to make one stop on the way.

39:50.447 --> 39:52.447
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh-ooh, ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

39:52.483 --> 39:54.316
♪ Put the gun down ♪

39:54.351 --> 39:57.319
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, put the gun down. ♪

39:59.227 --> 40:01.223
(buzzer sounds, lock clicks)

40:08.499 --> 40:10.915
♪ ♪

40:10.950 --> 40:12.067
Luc.

40:12.103 --> 40:13.468
Hey, baby.

40:15.059 --> 40:16.845
It's so good to see your face.

40:21.131 --> 40:22.896
They say I'm getting
out of here in the morning.

40:23.984 --> 40:25.713
I couldn't wait that long.

40:25.856 --> 40:26.922
♪ ♪

40:27.029 --> 40:29.096
They didn't want
to let me see you, but...

40:29.520 --> 40:31.945
Natalie doesn't take no for an answer.

40:32.322 --> 40:33.455
♪ ♪

40:33.490 --> 40:34.448
Lucky for me.

40:42.399 --> 40:46.468
Did they... ask you anything again?

40:47.153 --> 40:48.403
About that night?

40:50.696 --> 40:51.863
About us?

40:52.673 --> 40:53.914
No.

40:54.720 --> 40:56.519
I wouldn't say anything if they did.

40:56.635 --> 40:57.472
You know that.

40:57.872 --> 40:59.440
No one can know, Luc.

41:00.384 --> 41:03.385
♪ ♪

41:03.420 --> 41:04.441
Ever.

41:05.322 --> 41:07.256
No one will ever know.

41:08.045 --> 41:09.978
No one except you and me.

41:13.430 --> 41:14.790
It's our secret.

